{"TopicId":206187,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Persistent Equipment mod?","CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-31T10:09:50Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-31T10:09:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m sick of setting my crew\u0027s equipment to only find on a relaunch it\u0027s back to parachutes and EVA packs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a mod that fixes this? Or a way anybody knows of to change it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xt007","CreatedById":197003,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-31T16:34:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStock settings menu when you create a save, option for \u0022persistent loadout\u0022\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jacke","CreatedById":103694,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-31T22:36:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this may be fixed in the KSP Community Fixes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022163039\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4939426133\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/204002-18-112-kspcommunityfixes-bugfixes-and-qol-tweaks/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Axelord FTW","CreatedById":1896,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-01T23:50:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI got that, and I still sometime get that problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-02T02:12:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224071206\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206187\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221640968477\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197003\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xt007\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/31/2021 at 11:34 AM, Xt007 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStock settings menu when you create a save, option for \u0022persistent loadout\u0022\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat? This is an OPTION and the DEFAULT is \u0022screw over the player\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay I guess I really shouldn\u0027t be surprised but I\u0027m surprised at this one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-02T02:33:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Kerbal Persistent Equipment\u0022 sadly doesn\u0027t do what I want.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t want Jeb to always have the same loadout no matter what ship he\u0027s in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want seat 1 of vessel A to always have the same loadout no matter what kerbal is in the seat, and more importantly I want it remembered when loading the craft or reverting to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dave1904","CreatedById":153882,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-08T21:33:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224071773\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206187\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641090785\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/2/2022 at 3:33 AM, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Kerbal Persistent Equipment\u0022 sadly doesn\u0027t do what I want.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t want Jeb to always have the same loadout no matter what ship he\u0027s in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want seat 1 of vessel A to always have the same loadout no matter what kerbal is in the seat, and more importantly I want it remembered when loading the craft or reverting to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI understand. I just save the loadout in the craft inventory. Maybe add more inventory slots to command modules to get around the space issue.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}